OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Mon 27 Jul to Wed 5 AugFA
OL,6,Fchangeable period is likely overall,
OL,7,Fwith many areas likely to see a
OL,8,Fmixture of bright or sunny spells and
OL,9,Fsome rain at times. Northwestern areas
OL,10,Fare more likely to see the focus of
OL,11,Frainfall, but southeastern areas
OL,12,Fshould also see some showers.
OL,13,FConfidence becomes lower into the
OL,14,Fstart of August, but there are hints
OL,15,Fthat high pressure could return for a
OL,16,Ftime, which would mean dry conditions
OL,17,Fresuming, especially in the south.
OL,18,FWinds will be mostly light or
OL,19,Fmoderate, but occasionally fresh or
OL,20,Fstrong around some coasts, mainly in
OL,21,Fthe north and west. Temperatures will
OL,22,Fbe near or above normal, warmest in
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fthe south, and perhaps becoming very
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fwarm again by the start of August.
